        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Leith Hill Place | Dorking Wotton</placeName>
                    <date>Aug. 17 1872</date>
                    <seg type="supplemental">(return home on Wed)</seg>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I will tell all foreigners that you will supply them at £75 per 1000 copies.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> This sounds large, but after all I think you take an exaggerated view of the subject, for 1<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>-6<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> added to the price of the book will entirely cover this outlay.</p>
<p>I c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> not possibly have given many of the expressions by wood-block but I w<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> not have given so many photos had I forseen the cost.</p>
<p>I enclose a translation of M. Koch’s letter;<ref target="#foot.f2"/> &amp; will you be so kind as to act accordingly. I will write by this post to him &amp; tell him the price of the heliotypes.</p>
<p>I am very much obliged for all the great trouble you have taken in assisting me— | My dear Sir | yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8473.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from R. F. Cooke, 16 August 1872</ref> and n. 2.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The letter from Eduard Friedrich Koch and the translation of it have not been found.</note>
        </div>        
            
